<section id="introduction" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>For this post, I worked with a data set of 949 Pokémon, accessed from the TidyTuesday GitHub repository: <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/main/data/2025/2025-04-01/pokemon_df.csv" class="uri">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/main/data/2025/2025-04-01/pokemon_df.csv</a>. The data set contains 22 variables; the variables relevant to this post are <code>pokemon</code>, <code>attack</code>, <code>defense</code>, <code>base_experience</code>, and <code>hp</code>. <code>pokemon</code> is the Pokemon’s name (like Pikachu or Bulbasaur), <code>attack</code> is the Pokémon’s attack stat (which helps determine how much damage it’s attacks do), <code>defense</code> is the Pokémon’s defense stat (which helps determine how much damage opposing attacks deal), <code>base_experience</code> is the amount of experience the Pokémon yields upon being defeated in battle, and <code>hp</code> is the amount of health that the Pokémon has.</p>
