<section id="conclusion" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
<p>It is important to note that this data set only contains Pokémon from Generations 1 through 7. This means that the most recent games and their Pokémon are not represented. It is possible that Blissey has been dethroned in the newest Generations. With more time and more complex data, I would have liked to analyze Blissey’s move set, especially in the context of knowing her as a tank Pokémon.</p>
</section>
<section id="class-connections" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="class-connections">Class Connections</h2>
<p>I feel my visualizations are good ways of communicating information because I used color to add information to the plots and emphasize the important observations. I will note that my boxplot is quite squished, but because I was focusing on an outlier rather than the spread, I feel it is reasonable.</p>


